## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of recent empirical data and the inherent biases present in opinion pieces and critiques. Additionally, the complexity of economic systems means that isolating the effects of trickle-down policies from other economic factors can be challenging. Further research with updated data and broader economic models would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the long-term impacts of trickle-down economics.